<A NAME="chapterSkinSurfaceRef"></A><h1>3D Skin Surface Meshing<BR>
<I>Reference&nbsp;Manual</I></h1>

 

<p class="subtitle">Nico Kruithof</p>
<P>

Skin surfaces form a class of tangent continuous surfaces defined by a
set of balls and a scalar called the shrink factor. The skin surface
package constructs an triangular mesh isotopic to the skin surface,
using the algorithm described in [<A HREF="../biblio.html#Biblio_cgal:kv-mssct-05">KV05</A>]. The mesh is
stored in a <I><A HREF="../Polyhedron_ref/Class_Polyhedron_3.html#Cross_link_anchor_1110">CGAL::Polyhedron_3</A></I>.
<P>

